benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts - Retrieve an account by external key

covered: GET Valid Request coverage: multiple scenarios returning account by externalKey with default and with optional params (TC01 TC02 TC03 TC04 TC05 TC18 TC22 TC23 TC24 TC25)
Empty Response handling: 404 when no account exists (TC06) and 404 when empty database (TC17)
Query Parameters coverage: various combinations including externalKey, accountWithBalance, accountWithBalanceAndCBA, audit (TC01-TC05, TC08, TC09, TC10, TC14, TC15, TC16)
Authorization coverage: 401 for missing/invalid tokens (TC11, TC12)
Error handling for invalid inputs: 400 for invalid externalKey (TC08, TC14, TC15), 400 for invalid boolean (TC09), 400 for invalid audit (TC10)
Regression/edge cases: problematic externalKey (TC22), legacy compatibility (TC23), inconsistent data (TC24), time-based performance (TC20) and concurrency (TC21)
gaps: Pagination: No tests covering pagination for large datasets
Caching behavior: No tests validating ETag/Cache-Control headers
Authorization nuance: No explicit 403 (forbidden due to permissions) test
Rate limiting: No tests simulating rate limiting or throttling under load
Legacy or compatibility edge: few scenarios around backward compatibility beyond basic legacy key (TC23)
recommendations: Add pagination tests to ensure correct handling with large result sets
Add tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and cache invalidation behavior
Add explicit 403 Forbidden scenario for authorization with insufficient permissions
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests under high load or burst traffic
Add broader backward-compatibility tests beyond the basic legacy client scenario (e.g., different client versions)
